    ::::div{class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12"}
      :::::div{class="text-left"}
        ::::::h3{class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4"}
        For Mod Developers
        ::::::

        ```java
        // Basic usage - simple and clean
        FMODAPI.playEventSimple("event:/vehicles/engine", x, y, z);

        // Advanced usage with full control
        String instanceId = FMODAPI.playEvent("event:/weapons/gunshot",
                                             new Vec3D(x, y, z),
                                             1.0f, 1.2f);
        ```

        Integration is automatic - pause/resume and volume sync happen without any code changes!
      :::::

      :::::div{class="text-left"}
        ::::::h3{class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4"}
        For Users
        ::::::

        1. **Download** FMOD API from [Modrinth](https://modrinth.com/mod/fmod-api) or [CurseForge](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/fmod-api)
        2. **Install** FMOD Engine from [FMOD.com](https://www.fmod.com/download#fmodengine)
        3. **Drop** FMOD API JAR into your mods folder
        4. **Play** - everything works automatically!

        Optional: Configure via Mods â†’ FMOD API â†’ Config
